      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Walking between terminals at Heathrow can be a bit like navigating a maze, but it's not impossible. The airport has a network of walkways and tunnels that connect the terminals, but it's not always straightforward.\n\nIn your case, since you have a 90-minute layover, you'll want to make sure you can get from one terminal to the other quickly. Heathrow's Terminal 2, where you'll likely be arriving from JFK, is connected to Terminal 5 (T5) by a short walkway, but if you're transferring to a different terminal, it might be more complicated.\n\nThe airport's website recommends taking the Tube (London's metro system) or a bus to get between terminals. The Tube is the most convenient option, but it might be a bit of a gamble if you're trying to make a tight connection. The buses, on the other hand, are more reliable, but they can be slower.\n\nIt's worth noting that Heathrow's Terminal 2 and Terminal 3 are connected by a short walkway, but Terminal 2 and Terminal 5 are not. If you're transferring to T5, you'll need to take the Tube or a bus to get there.\n\nAs for the distance,",
